description: Boxers, get ready to fight with this workout routine to build brute strength, rapid-fast reflexes, and superhuman endurance.
review: Amazing and super friendly staff that really knows their stuff. Best gym in Austin to actually learn Muay Thai while getting a helluva workout!

description: The great majority of boxers today still run 4 or 5 miles on a daily basis. Boxing is anaerobic in nature.
review: Great gym with great instructors, great equipment , and also a great environment to be in doing the kind of training we do. I highly recommend this to any level of experience when wanting to get in there and learn.

description: Boxers should eat natural carbohydrates, such as those found in sweet potatoes, peas, beans, wholegrain bread, fruits and honey.
review: This place is awesome. The atmosphere is friendly and inviting. The coaches work with you and very hands on with clients.

description: Timeboxing is a very simple and popular time management technique that can help you take better control over your schedule.
review: They hosted a nice charity seminar today to help a local martial artist raise money for cancer treatment. Great people!

description: Boxing is not exclusive to elite athletes and exercise enthusiasts. Everyone can enjoy the many benefits boxing has on the body.
review: I have been training at ELITE for about 6 months and i love it, they push you to be better in a fun and engaging way.The gym is incredibly supportive and treats you like family.

description: A proper boxing stance is what separates the great boxers from the average boxers and footwork determines the speed of a boxer.
review: First time taking a boxing class today. It was awesome. I was greeted by Nick. He was very informative about the membership they offer and attentive. I had so much fun.

description: Whatever you decide, the main thing is to give yourself at least 1 day a week off. That's the minimum requirement.
review: ELITE Boxing has been a great place to take my boys learn a new activity! They're typically enrolled in football and baseball. Introducing them to boxing has been an extra treat for them as they love the teachers and the friends they meet.

description: You need to be fresh and available. It is important to train regularly but in the two weeks preceding the fight (or at least one).
review: Have been attending on and off for several years. Great staff and high quality instruction. Would definitely recommend.
